"""
WHAT: Docker Compose configuration for CortexDocs ∞ local development.
WHY: Orchestrates PostgreSQL, backend FastAPI, and frontend Next.js services.
     Single command to spin up the entire system.
WHEN: Used for local development and testing.
WHERE: docker-compose.yml (project root)
HOW: PostgreSQL 16 with named volume, backend with .env binding, frontend with build context.
ALTERNATIVES CONSIDERED:
  - Kubernetes: Overkill for local development.
  - Docker run scripts: Less maintainable than compose.
  - Podman: Less adoption, Docker compatibility layer needed.
TRADEOFFS:
  - All services on single host — no horizontal scaling.
  - Container networking adds ~1ms latency vs bare metal.
  - Volume mounts for persistence — manual backup needed.
"""
